properties.sex: Taxfilers are people who filed a tax return for the reference year and were alive at the end of the year.

Information on the data source, the historical availability, definitions of the terms used, and the geographies available can be found at http://www.statcan.gc.ca/imdb-bmdi/4105-eng.htm. For questions and comments, contact income@statcan.gc.ca, Income Statistics Division, Client Services, Jean Talon Building, 5th Floor, Ottawa, Ontario K1A 0T6.
Dependent is a member of a family who did not file a personal income tax return for the referenced year.

Marital status is reported by taxfilers on their personal income tax return. Characteristics such as marital status are as of December 31 of the reference year. All dependent children are given a marital status of single.
Prior to 2007, the sex of dependent children is not known. For this reason, the information by sex does not add up to the total shown.
Married includes persons who indicated this marital status on their personal income tax return. Persons in common-law couples are not included.
Characteristics such as age are as of December 31 of the reference year.

The census metropolitan area (CMA) of Ottawa-Gatineau straddles the provincial borders of Ontario and Quebec. Three census agglomerations (CA) also straddle provincial borders: Campbellton straddles New Brunswick and Quebec, Hawkesbury straddles Ontario and Quebec, and Lloydminster straddles Alberta and Saskatchewan. Data for the combined provincial parts are provided at the end of the list of CMAs and CAs. Prior to 2008, data for the two parts of the Ottawa-Gatineau CMA may be added together to provide a total for the area, with the exception of medians, percentages, indexes and averages.
